## Country-Specific Mappings (reference)

| Concept | Canada | United States |
|---|---|---|
| Tax-advantaged savings | RRSP, TFSA, RESP, FHSA | 401k, IRA, HSA, 529 |
| Government benefits | CCB, EI, OAS, GST credit | Social Security, Medicaid, SNAP |
| Rate authority | Bank of Canada | Federal Reserve |
| Inflation data | Statistics Canada CPI | Bureau of Labor Statistics CPI |
| Household benchmarks | StatsCan Survey of Household Spending | US Consumer Expenditure Survey |
| Real estate data | HouseSigma, Zolo, CMHC | Zillow, Redfin, FHFA |
| HISA products | EQ Bank, Oaken, Wealthsimple | Ally, Marcus, SoFi |
| Mortgage context | CMHC, stress test, 5yr renewal cycle | 30yr fixed dominant, refi triggers |
| Investment index | TSX Composite | S&P 500 |

---

## Implementation Priority (when ready to build)

1. **`userProfile` document** — country, region, familySize, birthYear (unlocks categories 2, 3, 7, 8)
2. **Country inference on first parse** — auto-set profile.country from bank name
3. **Hardcode tax calendar** — RRSP/TFSA/CRA (CA) and IRA/401k/IRS (US) deadlines — free wins for category 3
4. **`referenceData/{country}` collection** — shared, not per-user; refreshed by scheduled job
5. **Pass country into insights prompt** — one prompt, country-aware AI output (not two separate prompts)
